hERG Activity Assay: Compounds were tested for inhibition of the human ether a go-go related gene (hERG) K+ channel using IonWorks patch clamp electrophysiology at Essen BioScience. 8-Point concentration-response curves of the effect of compound on hERG current as a percentage of pre-compound signal were generated using 3-fold serial dilutions from 11 μM and results are reported as IC50 in μM.

hERG Inhibition Activity Assay: 1. CHO-hERG cells which have been incubated overnight were added with sample buffer and incubated for 90 minutes at room temperature in darkness.2. The sample buffer was removed and assay buffer was added.3. The compound is added to the cell plate and incubated for 20 minutes in darkness.4. Cell plate was placed into FDSS. The fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 10 seconds. Exciting buffer was added to the cells at the 10th second and the fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 180 seconds5. Data were processed.

hERG Inhibition Activity Assay: 1. CHO-hERG cells which have been incubated overnight were added with sample buffer and incubated for 90 minutes at room temperature in darkness.2. The sample buffer was removed and assay buffer was added.3. The compound is added to the cell plate and incubated for 20 minutes in darkness.4. Cell plate was placed into FDSS. The fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 10 seconds. Exciting buffer was added to the cells at the 10th second and the fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 180 seconds5. Data were processed.

The fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 10 seconds. Exciting buffer was added to the cells at the 10th second and the fluorescence signal was recorded every second for 180 seconds5. Data were processed.
